    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im looking at some portland zoning stuff for a client. we have this corner lot in a residential zone and we're trying to see if a small corner grocery/convenience store is allowed under mixed-use regs. specifically, i need to know how the setback requirements work if the building is right on the property line near the intersection. thanks.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Zoning regulations, especially when you're dealing with a corner lot and mixed-use, can be tricky. You need to look at the specific Portland zoning code for that particular zone, but generally, when you're right on the property line at an intersection, the setback rules can get a bit more complicated, often involving \"zero lot line\" exceptions or specific corner lot overlays. It's always best to pull up the official text, or better yet, have a local land-use expert look at it. They'll know exactly how the city's rules treat those tricky corners.",
